# Training Planner — Frontend Design System

Before implementing any UI, read the full reference files in `/refs/`:
- `styles.css` — all CSS custom properties and component classes
- `StyleGuide.html` — visual usage of every token and component
- PNG screenshots — page-level layout targets

Use these as the source of truth. The summary below is for quick decisions only.

---

## Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js 14 (App Router)
- **Language:** TypeScript
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS + CSS Modules where needed, always extending from design tokens
- **Components:** shadcn/ui as base, always restyled to match this design system — never use shadcn defaults unstyled
- **Icons:** lucide-react
- **Fonts:** loaded via `next/font/google` — Plus Jakarta Sans + JetBrains Mono

---

## Design Tokens

All tokens are defined in `/refs/styles.css` as CSS custom properties on `:root`. Never hardcode colors or use arbitrary Tailwind values that conflict with these. Extend `tailwind.config.ts` to map these tokens.

### Colors

| Token | Value | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| `--bg` | `#f8f9f2` | Page background |
| `--bg-tint` | `#f3f6e6` | Subtle tinted areas |
| `--surface` | `#ffffff` | Cards, modals |
| `--surface-2` | `#fbfcf6` | File chips, nested surfaces |
| `--border` | `rgba(28,31,51,0.08)` | Default borders |
| `--border-strong` | `rgba(28,31,51,0.14)` | Emphasized borders |
| `--ink` | `#1c1f33` | Primary text |
| `--ink-2` | `#6b7280` | Secondary text, labels |
| `--ink-3` | `#9ca3af` | Tertiary, placeholders |
| `--accent` | `#DBFD6B` | Primary action, highlights |
| `--accent-ink` | `#1c1f33` | Text on accent background |
| `--accent-soft` | `rgba(219,253,107,0.18)` | Pills, washes |
| `--accent-soft-2` | `rgba(219,253,107,0.35)` | Hover fills |
| `--pos` | `#00a878` | Passed / positive states |
| `--pos-soft` | `rgba(0,168,120,0.12)` | Positive backgrounds |
| `--neg` | `#fb3640` | Failed / negative states |
| `--neg-soft` | `rgba(251,54,64,0.10)` | Negative backgrounds |
| `--blue` | `#5a7df0` | Analysis & Design tag |
| `--muted` | `#b5b8a8` | Transversal tag |

### Page Background

Always apply this gradient on the root page wrapper — never a flat color:
```css
background:
  radial-gradient(60% 50% at 100% 0%, rgba(219,253,107,0.32) 0%, rgba(219,253,107,0) 60%),
  radial-gradient(40% 40% at 0% 100%, rgba(219,253,107,0.10) 0%, rgba(219,253,107,0) 70%),
  var(--bg);
```

### Shadows

```css
--shadow-sm: 0 1px 2px rgba(28,31,51,.04), 0 1px 3px rgba(28,31,51,.04);
--shadow-md: 0 1px 2px rgba(28,31,51,.04), 0 8px 24px rgba(28,31,51,.06);
--shadow-lg: 0 2px 4px rgba(28,31,51,.04), 0 24px 48px rgba(28,31,51,.10);
```

### Border Radius

```css
--radius-sm: 8px;   /* file chips */
--radius-md: 12px;  /* modals, gates */
--radius-lg: 16px;  /* cards */
--radius-xl: 20px;  /* large containers */
```

